Cell["\<\
These points are useful for:
\t\[Bullet]\tevaluating symbolic modular expressions numerically,
\t\[Bullet]\ttesting derivatives at special loci,
\t\[Bullet]\tcomparing the behaviour of truncated Fourier expansions at \
special points of moduli space.
A typical workflow is to first replace symbolic modular forms using \
PrecomputedRules[n], and then evaluate the resulting expression at one of the \
fixed points.\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.982061426851543*^9, 3.982061440517064*^9}, {
  3.982122889173676*^9, 
  3.982122889680395*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"6506183b-01ab-4d66-8ee4-\
3badb41f9d3c"],

